# Maximum Likelihood Estimation

This repository contains the implementation of the exercises developed in the **Maximum Likelihood Estimation** module for Deep Learning.

## 📚 Topics Covered

- Gaussian (Normal) Distribution
- Probability Density Function (PDF)
- Likelihood
- Negative Log-Likelihood (NLL)
- Sum of Squared Errors (SSE)
- Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE)
- Gaussian Regression
- NumPy implementation of statistical models

## 🛠️ Technologies

- Python 3
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Jupyter Notebook

## 📂 Repository Contents

- `3.1 Maximum Likelihood.ipynb`

## 🎯 Learning Objectives

- Implement the Gaussian probability density function from scratch.
- Compute likelihood and negative log-likelihood.
- Understand the relationship between maximum likelihood estimation and loss functions.
- Implement the Sum of Squared Errors (SSE).
- Gain intuition about probabilistic models used in machine learning.

